{"lemma":"فَرِيد","slug":"فَرِيد","root":"ف.ر.د","root_slug":"ف-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-د","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33444"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AF"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"alone, single"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sole, only"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"lonely"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"solitary"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"singular, unique, matchless, unrivaled, unparalleled, nonpareil, peerless, incomparable, nonesuch"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"one and only"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"particularly endowed with (+ genitive)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Fareed or Farid"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare فَرَدَ (farada, “to be single, to be alone; to be singular, to be unique”) and فَرُدَ (faruda, (same))."},"ipa":["/fa.riːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33444","headword_ar":"فَرِيدٌ","root":"frd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodN","text_ar":"فَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", former half, in two places: and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAdN","text_ar":"فُرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$a*orN","text_ar":"شَذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beads that divide the other beads of a string"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, A;) in the language of the 'Ajam [app. meaning Persians] called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAwarosaq","text_ar":"جَاوَرْسَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a word I do not find in any dictionary]: accord. to Ibráheem El-Harbee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$a*or","text_ar":"شَذْر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver, like pearls:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$a*or","text_ar":"شَذْر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that divide the pearls and gold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pearls that are strung, and divided by other things interposed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pearls that divide the pieces of gold in a necklace:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) one thereof is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariydapN","text_ar":"فَرِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, M, A, L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAy^idu","text_ar":"فَرَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, M, K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A precious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highly-esteemed, gem;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariydapN","text_ar":"فَرِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) as though it were the only one of its kind; (M, L;) or so called because unequalled; or because [it is a pearl] found alone in its shell: (MF:) and as some say, (S,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAy^idu","text_ar":"فَرَايِدُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ur~i","text_ar":"الدُّرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the large pearls."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intermediate vertebræ between the last of the six vertebræ that are next to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daA^oY","text_ar":"دَاْى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the neck and the six that are between these"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyd","text_ar":"فَرِيد"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rump-bone called the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajob","text_ar":"عَجْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAy^idu","text_ar":"فَرَايِدُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, L, K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariydapN","text_ar":"فَرِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the sing.] signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vertebra that projects from the part, of the back of a horse, that is next to the lumbar vertebrœ; intervening between the dorsal vertebræ and the lumbar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it projects in some horses. (M, L.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","L","K","S","A","MF"]}]}}